    "description": "Noda Corporation manufactures, processes, imports, and sells woody and inorganic building materials, medium-density fiberboard, and plywood products in Japan. The company provides building interior materials, including flooring, inner wall, fixture members, staircase members, framework, and step products; exterior substrate materials for motor use; and home furnishings and fixtures, such as interior and sliding doors, closets, opening frame members, front hall storage racks, home storage units, and other products, as well as handrail members. It also offers laminated wood bonded with braces and structural hi-best wood; and imports and sells ordinary, concrete forming, structural, and painted plywood, as well as coniferous plywood, south-sea lumber plywood, and other products. The company was formerly known as NODA PLYWOOD Mfg. Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Noda Corporation in 1989. Noda Corporation was founded in 1902 and is headquartered in Taito, Japan."
